This is Katello — a content and subscription management plugin for Foreman.

## Layout
- Plugin code: /home/vagrant/katello (Rails Engine)
- Runs from: /home/vagrant/foreman (host app)
- All Ruby namespaced under Katello::, DB tables prefixed katello_

## Key Directories
- Models (~134): app/models/katello/
- API Controllers: app/controllers/katello/api/v2/
- Dynflow Actions: app/lib/actions/katello/
- Services: app/services/katello/
- Views (RABL): app/views/katello/api/v2/
- Routes: config/routes/api/
- Permissions: lib/katello/permissions/
- React UI: webpack/
- Tests: test/ (minitest with factories)

## Running Things
- Rails console: cd /home/vagrant/foreman && bundle exec rails console
- All tests: cd /home/vagrant/foreman && bundle exec rake test:katello:test TESTOPTS="-v"
- Single test: cd /home/vagrant/foreman && bundle exec ruby -Itest /home/vagrant/katello/test/path/to/test.rb
- React tests: cd /home/vagrant/katello && npx jest webpack/path/to/test
- RuboCop: cd /home/vagrant/katello && bundle exec rubocop --parallel

## Services on This VM
- Foreman: https://localhost (Rails app)
- Pulp 3: https://localhost:24816
- PostgreSQL: foreman database
- Redis: background job backend
